originalText.text: I parked here to attend a matine showing of Wicked at the Gershwin theater on a Sunday.  The lot was not busy.  The attendant walked around the car with me to acknowledge any existing damage, and then asked us when we were coming back.  I had to give him my cell phone number to receive an electronic claim ticket.  We parked for 7 hours for $60.  I was very pleased with the experience.

originalText.text: Parked here last night so we could eat across the street. Paid for three hours of parking and when we left, half of our keys for our work office and home were missing from our car key ring. We realized this once we got home because they gave us the car back with it running and the keys already placed in the car so we didn’t notice it. I had to call out of work to drive back an hour and a half in horrible weather, paying tolls and city entry fare just to get our keys back and fix their mistake. The manager couldn’t tell us why this happened, and only apologized but would not issue a refund or credit. One person on the phone last night when we called to verify said “the keys were loose, sorry” WELL IF YOU KNEW THEY’RE LOOSE, PUT THEM BACK ON IF THEY FELL OFF!? This was a massive inconvenience and THEIR fault. Why were half of our keys missing?? Terrible business management and ethics to not offer anything for their bad service.

originalText.text:
Easy to get to out of the Lincoln Tunnel. Also easy to leave the city if you’re heading toward Lincoln tunnel or the FDR. The pull in / pull out of the garage was fairly easy as the street is usually pretty quiet.

The attendants are really nice and take good care of the cars. I pre paid my reservation and unfortunately you don’t get a refund if you leave earlier than you expected to, but I’d still recommend pre booking.

This is the garage I used for staying at the citizenM. Worth it!
